Thanks John, Short answer is no.

The bmc_command_recv tracks per command thread retries and returns FAIL_RETRY if the number of retries exceeds BMC__MAX_RECV_RETRIES.

maintenance/mtcBmcUtil.cpp -> bmc_command_recv

   if ( node_ptr->bmc_thread_ctrl.retries++ >= BMC__MAX_RECV_RETRIES )
   {
       print max retries lo reached
       return FAIL_RETRY
   }

This is true for all BMC commands. The FSMs need only compare return code to RETRY and keep calling bmc_command_recv until PASS or not RETRY is returned.

